content: Joined an online course on AI-driven market prediction models. The intersection of AI and blockchain is where I want to be.
Spent the day coding. Integrating AI into my trading algorithm is challenging but exciting. Every line of code feels like a step closer to my goals.
Networking pays off. Met a contact from Hong Kong, opened up possibilities for exploring international financial markets.
Quantum-secure blockchain is the future. Researching how to incorporate this into trading platforms. It's a complex challenge, but essential for long-term security.
Went on a date last night. Balancing work and personal life is tricky, but it's all part of finding that direction and purpose.
Developed a basic version of my trading algorithm. It's not perfect, but it's a start. Now, to refine it with AI integration for better market predictions.
Attended a workshop on financial regulatory technology. Compliance in trading is becoming crucial, and I'm considering a pivot in this direction.
Visited my mentor today. Shared my progress on the trading algorithm. His feedback was constructive; time to iterate and improve.
Taking a moment to reflect on these past six months. NYC's energy has fueled my drive to restart my career. I've made strides in high-frequency trading, but there's still so much to learn and do.
